The paper proposes a multi-agent reinforcement learning framework for power control in energy harvesting networks. This involves the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques and mean-field game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
